description:
src/lib.rs:231 'status == 429', 236 'status == 401', 276 'status == 404', 386 'status == 404'. Compare to secretx-hashicorp-vault/src/lib.rs:80 'status == reqwest::StatusCode::TOO_MANY_REQUESTS' and :206 'reqwest::StatusCode::NOT_FOUND'. The same workspace, two different conventions for the same operation.

Suggested rewrite:
  use reqwest::StatusCode;
  if status == StatusCode::TOO_MANY_REQUESTS { ... }
  if status == StatusCode::UNAUTHORIZED { ... }
  if status == StatusCode::NOT_FOUND { ... }

Engineering basis: a reader greps for 401 / 404 / 429 in this crate and finds raw integers; if the reader greps in vault they find symbolic constants. Cross-crate consistency reduces cognitive load; named constants are self-documenting (don't require remembering the integer).
